						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kṛishṇa III. Year 19: 958 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of ninety sheep by Tatpurusha bhaṭārar, a native of Kaḷakkuḍi for burning a perpetual lamp to the god of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr. He also donated one Īḻā lamp, apparently for the said purpose.</p>						

